{"id": 232089128, "title": "Late Kenneth Gbagi: Oshetigho Pays Condolences Visit To Family", "text": "Hon. Chief Michael Oshetigho Djegbe, the Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Ughelli South Local Government Area of Delta State, recently visited the family of the late Kenneth Gbagi to express his condolences. During his visit to the family in Oginibo, Oshetigho reflected on the significant role that Gbagi played in shaping his current position, emphasizing that he wouldn\u2019t be where he is today without Gbagi\u2019s support and mentorship. Describing Olorogun Kenneth Gbagi as a man who touched many lives through his work as a business mogul, politician, and traditional chief, Oshetigho highlighted the importance of emulating Gbagi\u2019s exemplary life. He offered words of advice to Gbagi\u2019s children, encouraging them to maintain unity, peace, and love among themselves to uphold their father\u2019s legacy and good reputation. Oshetigho concluded by praying for the soul of late Olorogun Kenneth Gbagi, asking for eternal rest in the bosom of the Lord. In response, Chief Emuobo Gbagi, the eldest son of the late Kenneth Gbagi, expressed gratitude to the PDP chairman for his visit and support during this difficult time.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"965\" height=\"438\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0056.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" srcset=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0056.jpg 965w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0056-300x136.jpg 300w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0056-768x349.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 965px) 100vw, 965px\" /></div>Hon. Chief Michael Oshetigho Djegbe, the Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Ughelli South Local Government Area of Delta State, recently visited the family of the late Kenneth Gbagi to express